\N<Boku>Hey, Grandpa. There's something I want to ask you,
can I?
\N<Grandfather>Hmm? What is it?

\N<Boku>Do you know the story about not swimming alone in
the waterfall beyond that river over there in the evening?

\N<Grandfather>Oh, that brings back memories. Yes, I know. I
heard it from my grandfather when I was young.
\N<Boku>What? Really?

\N<Grandfather>Ah, that's true. There's a legend that says
there's a river princess living in these mountains who
survives by devouring men's essence.

\N<Grandfather>They say the river princess sucks the souls
of children who approach the riverbank in the evening...
Well, it's just a superstition that means children shouldn't
go near the water's edge at dusk.

\N<Grandfather>Well... Actually, I had a strange experience
once on the riverbank at dusk when I was a child...

\N<Grandfather>I saw a girl with long white hair and pale
skin across the river, but as soon as I saw her, I lost
consciousness... After that, I was bedridden for three days,
it was quite a ordeal...

\N<Grandfather>I told everyone that I caught a summer cold
from sleeping on the riverbank and being feverish, but no
one believed me. But maybe, that was the river princess
after all...

\N<Grandfather>Well, that's a story from many decades ago.
Since then, I haven't approached the riverbank at dusk out
of fear. Thanks to that, I've been able to live a long life
without any accidents.
\N<Grandfather>You should be careful too.
\N<Boku>Yes.

\N<Boku>(Hmm... The story was long and I didn't quite
understand, but there's a girl by the riverbank in the
evening who devours men's essence...?)

\N<Boku>(I don't really understand what essence means, but
